code: import os import numpy as np import pandas as pd from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split import torch from torch.utils.data import Dataset, DataLoader import torch.nn as nn import torch.optim as optim from torchvision import transforms, models from PIL import Image from sklearn.metrics import roc_curve, auc # Configuration BATCH_SIZE = 64 IMG_SIZE = 256 EPOCHS = 3 SEED = 42 torch.manual_seed(SEED) # Data preparation def get_image_paths(): cover_ids = [f for f in os.listdir("input/Cover") if f.endswith(".jpg")] train_ids, val_ids = train_test_split(cover_ids, test_size=0.2, random_state=SEED) def build_split(ids): paths, labels = [], [] for img_id in ids: paths.extend( [ f"input/Cover/{img_id}", f"input/JMiPOD/{img_id}", f"input/JUNIWARD/{img_id}", f"input/UERD/{img_id}", ] ) labels += [0, 1, 1, 1] return paths, labels train_paths, train_labels = build_split(train_ids) val_paths, val_labels = build_split(val_ids) return (train_paths, train_labels), (val_paths, val_labels) # Dataset class class StegoDataset(Dataset): def __init__(self, paths, labels, transform=None): self.paths = paths self.labels = labels self.transform = ( transforms.Compose( [ transforms.Resize(IMG_SIZE), transforms.RandomHorizontalFlip(), transforms.RandomVerticalFlip(), transforms.ColorJitter(0.1, 0.1, 0.1), transforms.ToTensor(), transforms.Normalize([0.485, 0.456, 0.406], [0.229, 0.224, 0.225]), ] ) if transform else transforms.Compose( [ transforms.Resize(IMG_SIZE), transforms.ToTensor(), transforms.Normalize([0.485, 0.456, 0.406], [0.229, 0.224, 0.225]), ] ) ) def __len__(self): return len(self.paths) def __getitem__(self, idx): img = Image.open(self.paths[idx]).convert("RGB") return self.transform(img), self.labels[idx] # Model setup model = models.efficientnet_b0(pretrained=True) model.classifier[1] = nn.Linear(model.classifier[1].in_features, 1) device = torch.device("cuda" if torch.cuda.is_available() else "cpu") model = model.to(device) # Data loaders (train_paths, train_labels), (val_paths, val_labels) = get_image_paths() train_dataset = StegoDataset(train_paths, train_labels, transform=True) val_dataset = StegoDataset(val_paths, val_labels) train_loader = DataLoader( train_dataset, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=True, num_workers=4, pin_memory=True ) val_loader = DataLoader( val_dataset, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, num_workers=4, pin_memory=True ) # Training setup criterion = nn.BCEWithLogitsLoss() optimizer = optim.AdamW(model.parameters(), lr=1e-4, weight_decay=1e-5) scheduler = optim.lr_scheduler.OneCycleLR( optimizer, max_lr=1e-3, steps_per_epoch=len(train_loader), epochs=EPOCHS ) # Training loop for epoch in range(EPOCHS): model.train() for images, labels in train_loader: images, labels = images.to(device), labels.float().to(device) optimizer.zero_grad() outputs = model(images).squeeze() loss = criterion(outputs, labels) loss.backward() optimizer.step() scheduler.step() # Validation and metric calculation model.eval() val_preds, val_labels = [], [] with torch.no_grad(): for images, labels in val_loader: outputs = model(images.to(device)).squeeze().cpu().numpy() val_preds.extend(outputs) val_labels.extend(labels.numpy()) fpr, tpr, _ = roc_curve(val_labels, val_preds) split_idx = np.argmax(tpr >= 0.4) if split_idx == 0: weighted_auc = auc(fpr, tpr) * 2 / 1.4 else: auc_low = auc(fpr[:split_idx], tpr[:split_idx]) auc_high = auc(fpr[split_idx:], tpr[split_idx:]) - 0.4 * ( fpr[split_idx] - fpr[split_idx - 1] ) weighted_auc = (auc_low * 2 + auc_high) / 1.4 print(f"Weighted Validation AUC: {weighted_auc:.4f}") # Test predictions with corrected paths test_files = [f for f in os.listdir("input/Test") if f.endswith(".jpg")] test_paths = [os.path.join("input/Test", f) for f in test_files] test_dataset = StegoDataset(test_paths, [0] * len(test_paths)) test_loader = DataLoader(test_dataset, batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, num_workers=4) model.eval() test_preds = [] with torch.no_grad(): for images, _ in test_loader: outputs = model(images.to(device)).squeeze().cpu().numpy() test_preds.extend(outputs) # Create submission with proper filenames pd.DataFrame({"Id": test_files, "Label": test_preds}).to_csv( "submission/submission.csv", index=False )
